<li id="cite_note-GA-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-GA_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-GA_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSimmons2017" class="citation thesis cs1">Simmons, Brian (December 2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://getd.libs.uga.edu/pdfs/simmons_brian_w_201712_phd.pdf"><i>Coming out Mormon: An examination of religious orientation, spiritual trauma, and PTSD among Mormon and ex-Mormon LGBTQQA adults</i></a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>University of Georgia Theses and Dissertations</i> (PhD). Athens, Georgia: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Georgia" title="University of Georgia">University of Georgia</a>. p.&#160;65. <q>[A] current temple recommend [allows one] to participate in temple ordinances. In order to hold a current temple recommend, a person must attest to their ecclesiastical leaders that they maintain faith in the LDS Church, and live according to the standards (including no sexual activity outside of heterosexual marriage and abstaining from coffee, tea, alcohol, tobacco, and illicit drugs).</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Adissertation&amp;rft.title=Coming+out+Mormon%3A+An+examination+of+religious+orientation%2C+spiritual+trauma%2C+and+PTSD+among+Mormon+and+ex-Mormon+LGBTQQA+adults&amp;rft.inst=University+of+Georgia&amp;rft.date=2017-12&amp;rft.aulast=Simmons&amp;rft.aufirst=Brian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fgetd.libs.uga.edu%2Fpdfs%2Fsimmons_brian_w_201712_phd.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-GTT-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-GTT_9-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-GTT_9-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/manual/gospel-topics/temples?lang=eng">"Temples"</a>. <i>churchofjesuschrist.org</i>. LDS Church. June 2019<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=churchofjesuschrist.org&amp;rft.atitle=Temples&amp;rft.date=2019-06&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fmanual%2Fgospel-topics%2Ftemples%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
