<li id="cite_note-Scarlet-19"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Scarlet_19-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scarlet_19-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Scarlet_19-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFletcher_Stack2018" class="citation news cs1"><a href="/wiki/Peggy_Fletcher_Stack" title="Peggy Fletcher Stack">Fletcher Stack, Peggy</a> (November 30, 2018). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.sltrib.com/religion/2018/11/30/mormonisms-scarlet/">"<span class="cs1-kern-left"></span>'Mormonism's Scarlet Letter'? It's a mark on their membership that follows some gay Latter-day Saints throughout their lives"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Salt_Lake_Tribune" title="The Salt Lake Tribune">The Salt Lake Tribune</a></i>. Salt Lake City, Utah. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230201023158/https://www.sltrib.com/religion/2018/11/30/mormonisms-scarlet/">Archived</a> from the original on February 1, 2023 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Salt+Lake+Tribune&amp;rft.atitle=%27Mormonism%27s+Scarlet+Letter%27%3F+It%27s+a+mark+on+their+membership+that+follows+some+gay+Latter-day+Saints+throughout+their+lives&amp;rft.date=2018-11-30&amp;rft.aulast=Fletcher+Stack&amp;rft.aufirst=Peggy&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sltrib.com%2Freligion%2F2018%2F11%2F30%2Fmormonisms-scarlet%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
