<li id="cite_note-Curable-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Curable_20-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Curable_20-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Curable_20-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball1976" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer W.</a> (1976) [1969]. <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/miracleofforgive00kimb"><i>The Miracle of Forgiveness</i></a></span> (23rd print&#160;ed.). <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. p.&#160;82,86. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-88494-192-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-88494-192-7"><bdi>978-0-88494-192-7</bdi></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>[Homosexuality] is curable and forgivable. ... Certainly it can be overcome .... [T]o those who say that this practice ... is incurable, I respond: 'How can you say the door cannot be opened until your knuckles are bloody ...? It can be done.' ... Some have ... convinced themselves that they ... have no desire toward the opposite sex. ... [L]et this individual repent of his perversion, force himself to return to normal pursuits and interests ... with the opposite sex, and this normal pattern [heterosexual dating] can become natural again.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Miracle+of+Forgiveness&amp;rft.pages=82%2C86&amp;rft.edition=23rd+print&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1976&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-88494-192-7&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fmiracleofforgive00kimb&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Counselling-21"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Counselling_21-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Counselling_21-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKimball1964" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer W.</a> (July 10, 1964). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/PresidentKimballACounsellingProblemInTheChurch"><i>A Counselling Problem in the Church</i></a>. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. pp.&#160;13–14<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>We know such a disease [homosexuality] is curable.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Counselling+Problem+in+the+Church&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pages=13-14&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=1964-07-10&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2FPresidentKimballACounsellingProblemInTheChurch&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-lds92-22"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-lds92_22-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-lds92_22-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-lds92_22-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-lds92_22-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-lds92_22-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.qrd.org/qrd/religion/judeochristian/protestantism/mormon/mormon-homosexuality"><i>Understanding and Helping Those Who Have Homosexual Problems</i></a>. LDS Church. 1992<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">November 3,</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Understanding+and+Helping+Those+Who+Have+Homosexual+Problems&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.qrd.org%2Fqrd%2Freligion%2Fjudeochristian%2Fprotestantism%2Fmormon%2Fmormon-homosexuality&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Paradigm-23"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Paradigm_23-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Paradigm_23-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Paradigm_23-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Paradigm_23-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Paradigm_23-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Paradigm_23-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPrince2017" class="citation speech cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gregory_Prince" title="Gregory Prince">Prince, Gregory A.</a> (September 27, 2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20190328232753/https://thc.utah.edu/lectures-programs/mcmurrin-lecture/PRINCE-MCMURRIN%20LECTURE-protected.pdf"><i>Science vs. Dogma: Biology Challenges the LDS Paradigm of Homosexuality</i></a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> (Speech). Sterling M. McMurrin Lecture Series. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah" title="University of Utah">University of Utah</a> Tanner Humanities Center, Salt Lake City, Utah. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://thc.utah.edu/lectures-programs/mcmurrin-lecture/PRINCE-MCMURRIN%20LECTURE-protected.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on March 28, 2019<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Science+vs.+Dogma%3A+Biology+Challenges+the+LDS+Paradigm+of+Homosexuality&amp;rft.place=University+of+Utah+Tanner+Humanities+Center%2C+Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.date=2017-09-27&amp;rft.aulast=Prince&amp;rft.aufirst=Gregory+A.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fthc.utah.edu%2Flectures-programs%2Fmcmurrin-lecture%2FPRINCE-MCMURRIN%