<li id="cite_note-Weeds-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Weeds_27-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Weeds_27-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Weeds_27-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJones2018" class="citation news cs1">Jones, Morgan (February 7, 2018). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.deseret.com/2018/2/7/20639656/the-weeds-story-is-one-of-many-stories-of-lgbt-latter-day-saints-that-continue-to-be-written">"The Weeds' story is one of many stories of LGBT Latter-day Saints that continue to be written"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a></i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: LDS Church<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span>. <q>Today, [LDS] Family Services says it offers the following: 'We assist individuals and families as they respond to same-sex attraction. Our therapists do not provide what is commonly referred to as 'reparative therapy' or 'sexual orientation change efforts'.'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span></q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Deseret+News&amp;rft.atitle=The+Weeds%27+story+is+one+of+many+stories+of+LGBT+Latter-day+Saints+that+continue+to+be+written&amp;rft.date=2018-02-07&amp;rft.aulast=Jones&amp;rft.aufirst=Morgan&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deseret.com%2F2018%2F2%2F7%2F20639656%2Fthe-weeds-story-is-one-of-many-stories-of-lgbt-latter-day-saints-that-continue-to-be-written&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Unethical-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Unethical_28-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Unethical_28-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFishRussell2020" class="citation journal cs1">Fish, Jessica N.; Russell, Stephen T. (August 2020). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7349462">"Sexual Orientation and Gender Identity Change Efforts are Unethical and Harmful"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/American_Journal_of_Public_Health" title="American Journal of Public Health">American Journal of Public Health</a></i>. <b>110</b> (8): 1113–1114. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2105%2FAJPH.2020.305765">10.2105/AJPH.2020.305765</a>. <a href="/wiki/PMC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMC (identifier)">PMC</a>&#160;<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7349462">7349462</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32639919">32639919</a>. <q>With substantial evidence of serious harms associated with exposure to [sexual orientation and gender identity change efforts (SOGICE)] particularly for minors, 21 states (and multiple cities and counties) have passed bipartisan laws or regulations prohibiting SOGICE. ... Furthermore, compared with LGBTQ youths with no exposure, those exposed to SOGICE showed 1.76 times greater odds of seriously considering suicide, 2.23 times greater odds of having attempted suicide, and 2.54 times greater odds of multiple suicide attempts in the previous year.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Journal+of+Public+Health&amp;rft.atitle=Sexual+Orientation+and+Gender+Identity+Change+Efforts+are+Unethical+and+Harmful&amp;rft.volume=110&amp;rft.issue=8&amp;rft.pages=1113-1114&amp;rft.date=2020-08&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7349462%23id-name%3DPMC&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F32639919&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2105%2FAJPH.2020.305765&amp;rft.aulast=Fish&amp;rft.aufirst=Jessica+N.&amp;rft.au=Russell%2C+Stephen+T.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7349462&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-SOCE2-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE2_29-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE2_29-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE2_29-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE2_29-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE2_29-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGalliherBradshawHydeDehlin2015" class="citation journal cs1">Galliher, Renee; Bradshaw, William; Hyde, Daniel; <a href="/wiki/John_Dehlin" title="John Dehlin">Dehlin, John P.</a>; Crowell, Katherine (April 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/260873307">"Sexual orientation change efforts among current or former LDS Church members"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Counseling_Psychology" title="Journal of Counseling Psychology">Journal of Counseling Psychology</a></i>. <b>62</b> (2): 95–105. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1037%2Fcou0000011">10.1037/cou0000011</a>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24635593">24635593</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/ResearchGate" title="ResearchGate">ResearchGate</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Counseling+Psychology&amp;rft.atitle=Sexual+orientation+change+efforts+among+current+or+former+LDS+Church+members&amp;rft.volume=62&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=95-105&amp;rft.date=2015-04&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1037%2Fcou0000011&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F24635593&amp;rft.aulast=Galliher&amp;rft.aufirst=Renee&amp;rft.au=Bradshaw%2C+William&amp;rft.au=Hyde%2C+Daniel&amp;rft.au=Dehlin%2C+John+P.&amp;rft.au=Crowell%2C+Katherine&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F260873307&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-SOCE-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE_30-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE_30-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SOCE_30-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFDehlin2015" class="citation thesis cs1"><a href="/wiki/John_Dehlin" title="John Dehlin">Dehlin, John P.</a> (2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://digitalcommons.usu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=5314&amp;context=etd"><i>Sexual Orientation Change Efforts, Identity Conflict, and Psychosocial Health Amongst Same-Sex Attracted Mormons</i></a> (PhD). <a href="/wiki/Utah_State_University" title="Utah State University">Utah State University</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 26,</span> 2023</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Adissertation&amp;rft.title=Sexual+Orientation+Change+Efforts%2C+Identity+Conflict%2C+and+Psychosocial+Health+Amongst+Same-Sex+Attracted+Mormons&amp;rft.inst=Utah+State+University&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft.aulast=Dehlin&amp;rft.aufirst=John+P.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.usu.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D5314%26context%3Detd&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Conservative_Christian_Identity-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Conservative_Christian_Identity_31-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Conservative_Christian_Identity_31-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPhillips2005" class="citation book cs1">Phillips, Rick (2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.academia.edu/9832128"><i>Conservative Christian Identity &amp; Same-Sex Orientation: The Case of Gay Mormons</i></a>. Frankfurt, Germany: <a href="/wiki/Peter_Lang_(publisher)" title="Peter Lang (publisher)">Peter Lang Publishing</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0820474809" title="Special:BookSources/978-0820474809"><bdi>978-0820474809</bdi></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Academia.edu" title="Academia.edu">Academia.edu</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Conservative+Christian+Identity+%26+Same-Sex+Orientation%3A+The+Case+of+Gay+Mormons&amp;rft.place=Frankfurt%2C+Germany&amp;rft.pub=Peter+Lang+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=978-0820474809&amp;rft.aulast=Phillips&amp;rft.aufirst=Rick&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.academia.edu%2F9832128&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
