<li id="cite_note-Parents-40"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Parents_40-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Parents_40-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Parents_40-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://search.lib.byu.edu/byu/record/lee.2255698"><i>Understanding and Changing Homosexual Orientation Problems</i></a>. LDS Church. 1981. pp.&#160;6–7. <q>If the father is rejecting or uninvolved, or if the mother becomes 'smothering' in an attempt to fill the void left by a weak father, the child can become ... a prime candidate for homosexual (homoerotic) thoughts, feelings, and behaviors.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Understanding+and+Changing+Homosexual+Orientation+Problems&amp;rft.pages=6-7&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.lib.byu.edu%2Fbyu%2Frecord%2Flee.2255698&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
