<li id="cite_note-Reparative-63"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Reparative_63-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBinghamPotts1993" class="citation journal cs1">Bingham, Ronald D.; Potts, Richard W. (April 1, 1993). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?1&amp;article=1344&amp;context=irp">"Homosexuality: An LDS Perspective"</a>. <i>Issues in Religion and Psychotherapy</i>. <b>19</b> (1). <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>: 14. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20221104052042/http://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?1&amp;article=1344&amp;context=irp">Archived</a> from the original on November 4, 2022<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span>. <q>Most Church leaders seem to agree that professional counselors can play an important role in helping individuals experiencing problems with homosexuality. ... The church has supported efforts of the LDS Social Services and other consulting professionals to research the issues and to offer a reparative therapy approach which assumes that homosexual behavior can be changed.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Issues+in+Religion+and+Psychotherapy&amp;rft.atitle=Homosexuality%3A+An+LDS+Perspective&amp;rft.volume=19&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=14&amp;rft.date=1993-04-01&amp;rft.aulast=Bingham&amp;rft.aufirst=Ronald+D.&amp;rft.au=Potts%2C+Richard+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fscholarsarchive.byu.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3F1%26article%3D1344%26context%3Dirp&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" cla