<li id="cite_note-64"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-64">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWoodruff2016" class="citation news cs1">Woodruff, Daniel (March 15, 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://kutv.com/news/local/new-book-details-lds-teens-humiliating-gay-conversion-therapy-in-utah">"New book details LDS teen's 'humiliating' gay conversion therapy in Utah"</a>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/CBS" title="CBS">CBS</a>. <a href="/wiki/KUTV" title="KUTV">KUTV</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span>. <q>The church denounces any therapy that subjects an individual to abusive practices.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=New+book+details+LDS+teen%27s+%27humiliating%27+gay+conversion+therapy+in+Utah&amp;rft.date=2016-03-15&amp;rft.aulast=Woodruff&amp;rft.aufirst=Daniel&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fkutv.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fnew-book-details-lds-teens-humiliating-gay-conversion-therapy-in-utah&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
