<li id="cite_note-Report-154"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Report_154-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Report_154-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://news.byu.edu/https:/brightspotcdn.byu.edu/1e/9f/3cfd38434e508ab9d421bf55f7ed/campus-climate-report-f2017.pdf">"Report on the Campus Climate Survey on Sexual Assault"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>news.byu.edu</i>. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>. November 2017. p.&#160;2. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220111233018/https://news.byu.edu/https:/brightspotcdn.byu.edu/1e/9f/3cfd38434e508ab9d421bf55f7ed/campus-climate-report-f2017.pdf">Archived</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> from the original on January 11, 2022<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span>. <q>The online survey was conducted in spring 2017. Email invitations were sent to 29,471 BYU students; 13,784 (48%) started the survey and 12,602 completed the survey, for a response rate of 43%. Demographic data revealed the survey participants to be very similar to the broader BYU population in terms of gender, ethnicity, year in school, and other measures. Key demographics include the following: ... Gender: 52% male, 48% female, and 0.2% transgender or other.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=news.byu.edu&amp;rft.atitle=Report+on+the+Campus+Climate+Survey+on+Sexual+Assault&amp;rft.pages=2&amp;rft.date=2017-11&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.byu.edu%2Fhttps%3A%2Fbrightspotcdn.byu.edu%2F1e%2F9f%2F3cfd38434e508ab9d421bf55f7ed%2Fcampus-climate-report-f2017.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Survey-155"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Survey_155-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Survey_155-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKlundtEreksonLynnBrown2021" class="citation journal cs1">Klundt, Jared S.; Erekson, David M.; Lynn, Austin M.; Brown, Hannah E. (March 1, 2021). <span class="id-lock-subscription" title="Paid subscription required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0191886920306668">"Sexual minorities, mental health, and religiosity at a religiously conservative university"</a></span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Personality_and_Individual_Differences" title="Personality and Individual Differences">Personality and Individual Differences</a></i>. <b>171</b>: 110475. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.paid.2020.110475">10.1016/j.paid.2020.110475</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISSN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISSN (identifier)">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/issn/0191-8869">0191-8869</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:228862206">228862206</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 27,</span> 2023</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/ScienceDirect" title="ScienceDirect">ScienceDirect</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Personality+and+Individual+Differences&amp;rft.atitle=Sexual+minorities%2C+mental+health%2C+and+religiosity+at+a+religiously+conserva