<li id="cite_note-168"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-168">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWilliams2012" class="citation magazine cs1">Williams, Troy (April 19, 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20160301014032/http://saltlakemagazine.com/blog/welcome-to-the-gayborhood/">"Welcome to the Gayborhood"</a>. <i>Salt Lake Magazine</i>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://slmag.com/blog/welcome-to-the-gayborhood/">the original</a> on March 1, 2016 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>The destinies of Mormons and gays were becoming intertwined in the national discourse, providing creative fodder for theatrical productions including the 2011 Tony Award winner 'The Book of Mormon' in which Elder McKinnley, echoing the teachings of Boyd K. Packer, would encourage other gay Mormons to 'Turn it off' like a light switch.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Salt+Lake+Magazine&amp;rft.atitle=Welcome+to+the+Gayborhood&amp;rft.date=2012-04-19&amp;rft.aulast=Williams&amp;rft.aufirst=Troy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fslmag.com%2Fblog%2Fwelcome-to-the-gayborhood%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHomosexuality+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
